 :tx/rationale "LIVESTORE PLAN REVISION (Session 039 deep review): Five architectural gaps found. (1) INIT PATH: LiveStore::open() fails on non-existent .braid. Need LiveStore::create(path) for braid init — creates DiskLayout, writes genesis+schema txn files, then constructs LiveStore from the new store. This is the bootstrap path. (2) DIRTY FLAG OPTIMIZATION: Serializing store.bin on EVERY write_tx adds N*100ms per command. harvest does 5+ writes = 500ms of serialization. Fix: LiveStore tracks dirty:bool flag. write_tx marks dirty=true but does NOT serialize. LiveStore::flush() serializes if dirty. Drop impl calls flush(). Commands that need cache fresh for another process (status returning to agent) call flush() explicitly. This reduces serialization from N-per-command to 1-per-command. (3) STALE CACHE HOTFIX URGENCY: The fitness.json/coherence.json bugs are LIVE RIGHT NOW. LIVESTORE-HOTFIX (t-449ec46d) should be implemented BEFORE any LiveStore work. (4) BACKWARD COMPAT: Old store.bin files must remain readable after LiveStore deployment. Add a test that deserializes a known-good store.bin from the current system. (5) E2E LOGGING: LIVESTORE-TEST E2E script needs structured logging with timestamps at every assertion point so failures show exactly WHERE and WHEN things broke, not just that they broke."
